simlarly 
'Alice' * 'Bob' # won't work. python can't multiply 2 str's

variable naming
===============
special cahr like $,' not permitted
begin with numbers not permitted
sapces are not allowed
hypens are not allowed

can use _ inbetween
can use uppercase and lowecase
can use numbers except beginning

int(), str(), float()
========================
if want to concatenate 29. must pass the value to str. because line#9. 
concatenate_methode = 'Hello' + str(29) + 'years old'
